-- Romania Utility Water Plant Contract Goes to Four Firms
-- B y   I r i n a   S a v u
-- 2013-04-29T11:58:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-04-29/romania-utility-water-plant-contract-goes-to-four-firms.html
Apa Canal SA, a Romania utility,
awarded a 41.4 million-lei ($12.5 million) contract for water
infrastructure works in the eastern county of Galati.  The contract went to the Romanian companies Tancrad SRL and
Escalia Craus SA,  Biogest International GmbH  of  Germany  and
Bulgaria’s Glavbolgarstroy AD to build water-treatment plants in
the towns of Liesti and Pechea, according to an  April 27 notice 
on the European Union’s tender website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Irina Savu in Bucharest at 
 isavu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Randall Hackley at 
 rhackley@bloomberg.net  